Cell[TextData[{
 "FindBounce is a Mathematica package that computes the bounce configuration \
needed to compute \nthe false vacuum decay rate with multiple scalar fields. \
The physics background is described in the \npaper by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  ButtonBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Guada", ",", 
     RowBox[{"Maiezza", " ", "and", " ", "Nemev\[SHacek]ek"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"(", "2019", ")"}]}],
   BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
   ButtonData->{
     URL["https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.02227"], None},
   ButtonNote->"https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.02227"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d626c32a-3d8b-4d35-9003-62abaa054d19"],
 ". In this tutorial, we present examples of false \nvacuum decays in \
potential with multiple scalar fields.\n\nThe notebook cannot be saved, so it \
can be edited freely. \nContributions are welcome! "
}], "Text", \
"ApplicationNotes",ExpressionUUID->"cbec3db0-2e66-43a2-843e-64a3a32ef1e1"],

